aa(lp84
VFirst, we've got population.
p85
aVThe world today has 6.8 billion people.
p86
aVThat's headed up to about nine billion.
p87
aVNow, if we do a really great job on new vaccines,
p88
aVhealth care, reproductive health services,
p89
aVwe could lower that by, perhaps, 10 or 15 percent.
p90
aVBut there, we see an increase of about 1.3.
